From: GSI Builder <gsi@example.com>
Date: Sun, 2 Mar 2026 19:45:00 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] Remove HIDL fingerprint HAL from framework manifest

The framework_manifest.xml declared a HIDL biometrics.fingerprint v2.1
service via hwbinder transport. On AIDL-only Vendor15 targets,
hwservicemanager may not be running, causing SELinux denials
and stalled service lookups during boot.

Replace with an empty manifest to satisfy the build system
without declaring any HIDL services.

diff --git a/framework_manifest.xml b/framework_manifest.xml
index 1234567..89abcde 100644
--- a/framework_manifest.xml
+++ b/framework_manifest.xml
@@ -1,12 +1,4 @@
 <manifest version="1.0" type="framework">
-    <!-- For our Oppo/Realme friends -->
-    <hal>
-        <name>android.hardware.biometrics.fingerprint</name>
-        <transport>hwbinder</transport>
-        <version>2.1</version>
-        <interface>
-            <name>IBiometricsFingerprint</name>
-            <instance>default</instance>
-        </interface>
-    </hal>
+    <!-- HIDL fingerprint HAL removed: AIDL-only policy (Vendor15 GSI) -->
 </manifest>
